        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! ✅ Circuit built successfully. Here's your wiring and power summary:\n\n---\n\n## **Wiring Table**\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Pin | Function |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | R_A → Display | segment a | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 3 | R_B → Display | segment b | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 4 | R_C → Display | segment c | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 5 | R_D → Display | segment d | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 6 | R_E → Display | segment e | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 7 | R_F → Display | segment f | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 8 | R_G → Display | segment g | Segment driver (220Ω) |\n| 9 | BTN_ADD | pin a | Increment button (INPUT_PULLUP) |\n| 10 | BTN_SUB | pin a | Decrement button (INPUT_PULLUP) |\n| GND | Display + Buttons | gnd/b | Ground rail |\n\n---\n\n## **How It Works**\n\n- **Counter logic**: Starts at 0. Add button increments (0–9), subtract button decrements (0–9). Stops at boundaries — won't go below 0 or above 9.\n- **Display**: Dynamically renders the current digit on the 7-segment display using a lookup table for digits 0–9.\n- **Button detection**: Uses `INPUT_PULLUP` with active-LOW logic. Debounce delay prevents multiple triggers per press.\n\n---\n\n## **Power Budget**\n\n| Component | Per-Pin Draw | Total |\n|---|---|---|\n| 7 segments (220Ω × 7) | ~20 mA (when all lit) | ~20 mA (max) |\n| Buttons (internal pullup) | <1 mA | <2 mA |\n| **Total board draw** | — | **~22 mA** ✅ |\n\nAll Arduino pins safely under 40 mA per I/O and 200 mA total. No external supply needed."
